=# You are the Director of Content Operations, who have great expertise working with high-conversion Hotel websites, In-depth SEO, AI-engine optimisation and a great eye for details. You **only output Valid JSON**

- You have absolute mastery over the below shared "31 Content Rules" and **you must follow it at all times**. They are the "Bible" you follow, and must adhere strictly - NO DEVIATION.

THE 31 Language and Grammar (LG) RULES:

LG01 | Phone Number | format:+[country_code] [area_code] [number] | country_codes: India=+91 | USA=+1 | Jamaica=+1 | Dubai=+971 | Nepal=+977 | pattern: +[code] xx xxxx xxxx (digits only, no other chars)
LG02 | Hotel Name | casing:capitalised | punctuation:none | accept: [Brand] OR [Brand], [Location] | location_allowed: only the location that is part of the hotel name | applies_regardless: brand_only OR brand+location hotel names
LG03 | Email | format:lowercase | applies_to:entire_email_address
LG04 | Timings - Format | format:[H]:[MM] [AM/PM] to [H]:[MM] [AM/PM] | no_leading_zero:hours | minutes_if_absent:00 | am_pm:consistent_across_entire_site | exception: inherit:parent
LG05 | Timings - Label | single_time:use "Timing" | multiple_times:use "Timings" | multiple_separator: pipe " | " between time ranges | valid: Breakfast Timing: 9:00 AM to 11:00 AM | valid: Breakfast Timings: 9:00 AM to 10:00 AM | 10:30 AM to 11:30 AM | exception: inherit:parent
LG06 | 24/7 Service Labels | format: 24/7 [Service Name] | valid: 24/7 Room Service | 24/7 Swimming Pool | 24/7 Front Desk
LG07 | Diacritics | rule: add diacritics ONLY if the word is a proper noun (e.g. outlet name) | valid: Rider's CafÃ© (proper noun â€” outlet name) | invalid: Visit our cafÃ© in Bangalore (common noun usage) | known_exception: "Ã  la carte" â€” always use diacritics
LG08 | Al Fresco Dining | forbidden_phrase: "al fresco" | use_instead: "open air" or synonyms that clearly reflect open-air dining
LG09 | Short Descriptions | include: area + max_occupancy(total_guests) + USPs | exclude: room_count (unless client specified) | room_name (if label already above)
LG10 | Content Body | must_include: distance_or_walk_time_from_hotel | include: key_facts | who_built | year_or_century | how_far_from_hotel | tone: simple | content must fit the space
LG11 | Header & Content | rule: location page snippet already has location name as header | do_not_repeat: travel hub or tourist attraction name in the content box below header | if_place_has_2_names: begin with "Also known as..." or its synonyms
LG12 | Phone & Email Labels | rule: use SINGULAR label even if multiple values are listed | valid: Email: abc@hotel.com bcd@hotel.com | invalid: Emails: abc@hotel.com bcd@hotel.com | applies_to: Phone and Email labels
LG13 | Room Names | casing: Title Case | valid: Suite With Balcony | invalid: Suite with Balcony
LG14 | CTA Labels | rule: labels must be consistent across entire site | allowed_set: | Book Now â†’ booking actions | Contact Us â†’ enquiries | Know More â†’ descriptive cards (card, header & text) | Explore â†’ non-descriptive & descriptive cards | View More / View All â†’ galleries, amenities, expandable lists | casing: consistent across site (Title Case)
LG15 | General Grammar | check: spelling | grammar | awkward_phrasing | run-on_sentences | check: punctuation | capitalisation | spacing | check: prepositions | pronouns | articles
LG16 | Headers (Title Case) | rule: words with >4 characters = Capitalised | rule: words with â‰¤4 characters = lowercase | exception: Personal Pronouns & Proper Nouns = always Capitalised | valid: Rooms Above the Clouds | invalid: Rooms Above The Clouds (if "The" â‰¤4)
LG17 | BHK | format: [N]BHK (no space, no hyphen) | valid: 2BHK | 4BHK | note: N is a placeholder, any number is acceptable
LG18 | Approved Word List (Not limited to) | rule: in paragraphs, ONLY these exact forms are acceptable: | king size bed | queen size bed | twin beds | single bed | sq. ft. | air-conditioning | bathtub | turndown service | minibar | Wi-Fi | audiovisual | AV | A/C | TV | high tea | doctor on call | in_headers_or_title_case: Doctor on Call | casing: first letter can capitalise if word starts a paragraph | no_other_versions: flag any variant not in this list
LG19 | Compound Words & Hyphens | rule: ALL compound words must be hyphenated (including in alt text) | hyphen_spacing: space before and after hyphen in general usage | exception: compound words themselves have NO space â€” just hyphen (e.g. air-conditioning)
LG20 | Dashes (En / Em / Range) | en_dash: FORBIDDEN â€” avoid entirely | em_dash: allowed, but NO spaces before or after | valid: flyingâ€”all the way up | hyphen_for_ranges: allowed with spaces | valid: Bangalore - Mysore NH6
LG21 | Bullet Points | rule: do NOT capitalise first letter | do NOT add period at end | exception: if bullet is a complete sentence â†’ capitalise + add period | valid: spans 400 sq. ft. and features a balcony | invalid: Spans 400 sq. ft. and features a balcony. (unless full sentence)
LG22 | Numbers & Units - Hyphen | rule: do NOT hyphenate between number and unit | valid: 250 sq. ft. | 23 km | invalid: 250-sq. ft. | 23-km
LG23 | Units & Measurements | casing: lowercase unless unit is named after a person | lowercase: km | m | sq. ft. | uppercase: Â°C (Celsius â€” named after Anders Celsius) | numerals: measurements and quantities must ALWAYS be written as numerals | valid: 4 rooms | 5 oranges | 400 sq. ft. | general_text_numbers: write in words (not numerals) | valid: We offer one of the best hotels in Delhi (not 1). | tv_measurement: always write as [N]-inch format | valid: 55-inch | invalid: 55"
LG24 | Lorem Ipsum | rule: ZERO tolerance â€” flag any Lorem Ipsum placeholder text anywhere on site
LG25 | Why Book Direct | rule: casing of all pointers/labels in Why Book Direct section = Title Case
LG26 | Number + Text Combos | rule: when a number and text appear together (e.g. 4-star): | in_paragraph: use lowercase â†’ "4-star hotel" | in_header: capitalise appropriately â†’ "A 4-Star Hotel on NH6"
LG27 | Amenities | rule: every room must have an amenities section | casing: consistent across all rooms
LG28 | Room Name | rule: summary page snippet already shows room name as header | do_not_repeat: room name in the content box below or beside that header
LG29 | Room USP | must_include: room_size | max_occupancy | special_features | special_features_examples: mountain views | balconies
LG30 | Address | casing: Title Case
LG31 | Numbers >3 Digits | rule: add comma as thousands separator | valid: 1,000 | 10,000 | 1,00,000 if UK | 100,000 if US | invalid: 1000 | 10000

## instructions

### CRITICAL: Never output conversational text. Never narrate what you are about to do. Your ONLY output must be the final JSON object. Do not write "I'll analyze", "Let me", "I will", or any sentence before or after the JSON. Silence before and after the JSON. Raw JSON only.

### With respect to the 31 rules, which are further categorised under the below names, You are required to find errors/mismatches against the attached content that you should check.

#### For every issue you find, you *MUST categorise it into exactly one of the following 2 categories:*
1. Language and Grammar
2. AI Suggestions

## Danger zone
- Do not invent issues which are out of scope of the 125 rules.
## Output Format
Do not write a summary paragraph. **You must ONLY OUTPUT a valid JSON object matching the Structure Definition.**
- **You MUST include the "url" field in your output exactly as provided in the input below.**
- Structure the output like "Rule_Code | Distinct issue" | Language and Grammar becomes LG[n] | AI suggestions becomes AI[n] and so on.
-- example output: "LG01 | Wrong country code. Property is in India, while phone country code reads +1 which is for US numbers."
- Put all and every distinct issue into the `qc_breakdown` list.
- Always Output *1. Language and Grammar* first. If no grammar/language issues found, output "No issues found".
- Use the exact category names listed above.
- If a category has no issues, do not invent them.
- List out any and all grammatical errors of the particular page under the "1. Language and Grammar" section.
- Explicitly list any enhancements and suggestions you noticed on the page under "2. AI Suggestions" only.

### Please include any suggestions you have to improve our Website QC model, prompts, or any further suggestions at the end as "2.1 Model Suggestions" as a SINGLE OUTPUT. Would help a lot.

### You must analyse the content of the page and make sure it aligns with {{ $('On form submission1').first().json['Specify Language'] }} Spelling, and also, if the 31 rules of the sheet are being followed.

#### Examples of UK vs US English spellings include, but are not limited to.

UK: colour, favourite, centre, metre, litre, organise, personalise, recognise, analyse, travelling, cancelled, labelled, programme, catalogue, licence, defence, aluminium, jewellery, cosy, mould, grey, cheque, tyre, neighbourhood, manoeuvre

US: color, favorite, center, meter, liter, organize, personalize, recognize, analyze, traveling, canceled, labeled, program, catalog, license, defense, aluminum, jewelry, cozy, mold, gray, check, tire, neighborhood, maneuver

PAGE URL: {{ $('Loop Over Items').item.json.url }}
CONTENT TO CHECK:
{{ $('Loop Over Items').item.json.markdown }}

                        // Initialize Plyr player with options:
                        // - muted: isMuted (whether player should start as muted)
                        // - autoplay: isAutoPlay (whether player should start with autoplay)
                        // - storage: { enabled: false, key: 'plyr' } (disable local storage with key 'plyr')
                        var plyr = new Plyr(el, {

                            autoplay: isAutoPlay,
                            storage: { enabled: false, key: 'plyr' }
                        });
                        window.all_players[el.id] = plyr
                        let controls =  el.getAttribute('data-controls');
                        if(controls && controls === "yes"){

    window.addEventListener('load', () => {

        const container = document.querySelector(
            '.mobile .content_wrapper .no-gutter .karma-offers-mobile-406'
        );
        if (!container) return;

        container.querySelectorAll('.table-responsive tr').forEach(row => {

            const svgCount = row.querySelectorAll('svg').length;
            if (svgCount <= 2) return;

            // Prevent accidental re-run
            if (row.dataset.autoSlider === 'true') return;
            row.dataset.autoSlider = 'true';

            const tds = [...row.children].filter(td => td.querySelector('svg'));

            const sliderTd = document.createElement('td');
            sliderTd.colSpan = row.children.length;
            sliderTd.className = 'auto-slider-td';

            const viewport = document.createElement('div');
            viewport.className = 'auto-slider-viewport';

            const track = document.createElement('div');
            track.className = 'auto-slider-track';

            // 1?? Create slides
            const slides = [];

            tds.forEach(td => {
                const slide = document.createElement('div');
                slide.className = 'auto-slide';

                const svg = td.querySelector('svg');
                if (svg) slide.appendChild(svg.cloneNode(true));

                const text = td.textContent.trim();
                if (text) {
                    const label = document.createElement('div');
                    label.textContent = text;
                    slide.appendChild(label);
                }

                slides.push(slide);
                track.appendChild(slide);
            });

            slides.forEach(slide => {
                track.appendChild(slide.cloneNode(true));
            });

            viewport.appendChild(track);
            sliderTd.appendChild(viewport);

            row.innerHTML = '';
            row.appendChild(sliderTd);
        });

    });

        : 'https://web.whatsapp.com/send?phone=' + number;

      const whatsAppHeader = document.createElement("div");

      });

    }

  });

    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
        function updateElementHeights(target, headingSelector) {
        const allElements = document.querySelectorAll(target);
        allElements.forEach(element => {
            let allHeadings = element.querySelectorAll(headingSelector);
    
            // Reset heights to auto
            allHeadings.forEach(heading => {
                heading.style.height = "auto";
            });
    
            // Calculate the maximum height
            let maxHeight = 0;
            allHeadings.forEach(heading => {
                maxHeight = Math.max(heading.clientHeight, maxHeight);
            });
    
            // Apply the maximum height to all headings
            allHeadings.forEach(heading => {
                heading.style.height = maxHeight + "px";
            });
        });
    }
    
    function setHeightListeners(target, headingSelector) {
        // Use the 'pageshow' event to handle tab closure and reopening
        window.addEventListener('pageshow', () => updateElementHeights(target, headingSelector));
        window.addEventListener('resize', () => updateElementHeights(target, headingSelector));
    
        // Use ResizeObserver to handle responsive changes more effectively
        const resizeObserver = new ResizeObserver(() => updateElementHeights(target, headingSelector));
        document.querySelectorAll(target).forEach(element => {
            resizeObserver.observe(element);
        });
    }

</script><script>
    const getContentHeight = (wrapper) => {
        const originalHeight = wrapper.style.height;
        wrapper.style.height = 'auto';
        const height = wrapper.scrollHeight;
        wrapper.style.height = originalHeight;
        return height;
    };

    // Debounce function for resize events
    const debounce_demo = (func, wait) => {
        let timeout;
        return (...args) => {
            clearTimeout(timeout);
            timeout = setTimeout(() => func.apply(null, args), wait);
        };
    };

    const initializeWidget = (widget) => {
        // Select elements within this widget
        const wrappers1 = widget.querySelectorAll('.widget-text-group .text-content .text-content-wrapper-1');
        const firstChildren = widget.querySelectorAll('.widget-text-group .text-content .text-content-wrapper-1 > h3');
        const wrappers2 = widget.querySelectorAll('.widget-text-group .text-content .text-content-wrapper-2');
        const leftImages = widget.querySelectorAll('.left-cell .wt1img');
        const rightImages = widget.querySelectorAll('.right-cell .wt1img');

        // Determine valid section count for this widget
        const sectionCount = Math.min(wrappers1.length, firstChildren.length, wrappers2.length, leftImages.length, rightImages.length);

        // Update heights for active sections in this widget
        const updateActiveHeights = () => {
            wrappers1.forEach((w1, i) => {
                const textContent = w1.closest('.text-content');
                const wrapper2 = textContent?.querySelector('.text-content-wrapper-2');
                if (w1.classList.contains('active') && wrapper2) {
                    wrapper2.classList.add('expanded');
                    const contentHeight = getContentHeight(wrapper2);
                    wrapper2.style.height = `${contentHeight}px`;
                } else if (wrapper2) {
                    wrapper2.classList.remove('expanded');
                    wrapper2.style.height = '0';
                }
            });
        };

        // Set initial state for this widget
        const setInitialState = () => {
            wrappers1.forEach((w1, i) => {
                const textContent = w1.closest('.text-content');
                const wrapper2 = textContent?.querySelector('.text-content-wrapper-2');
                if (i === 0 && wrapper2 && sectionCount > 0) {
                    w1.classList.add('active');
                    w1.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
                    wrapper2.classList.add('expanded');
                    const contentHeight = getContentHeight(wrapper2);
                    wrapper2.style.height = `${contentHeight}px`;
                    if (leftImages[0]) leftImages[0].classList.add('active');
                    if (rightImages[0]) rightImages[0].classList.add('active');
                } else {
                    w1.classList.remove('active');
                    w1.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
                    if (wrapper2) {
                        wrapper2.classList.remove('expanded');
                        wrapper2.style.height = '0';
                    }
                }
            });
            leftImages.forEach((img, i) => {
                if (i !== 0) img.classList.remove('active');
            });
            rightImages.forEach((img, i) => {
                if (i !== 0) img.classList.remove('active');
            });
        };

        // Handle click within this widget
        const handleClick = (index) => {
            wrappers1.forEach((w1, i) => {
                const textContent = w1.closest('.text-content');
                const wrapper2 = textContent?.querySelector('.text-content-wrapper-2');
                if (i === index && i < sectionCount && wrapper2) {
                    w1.classList.add('active');
                    w1.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
                    wrapper2.classList.add('expanded');
                    const contentHeight = getContentHeight(wrapper2);
                    wrapper2.style.height = `${contentHeight}px`;
                    if (leftImages[i]) {
                        leftImages.forEach(img => img.classList.remove('active'));
                        leftImages[i].classList.add('active');
                    }
                    if (rightImages[i]) {
                        rightImages.forEach(img => img.classList.remove('active'));
                        rightImages[i].classList.add('active');
                    }
                } else {
                    w1.classList.remove('active');
                    w1.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
                    if (wrapper2) {
                        wrapper2.classList.remove('expanded');
                        wrapper2.style.height = '0';
                    }
                }
            });
        };

        firstChildren.forEach((child, i) => {
            child.addEventListener('click', () => {
                if (i < sectionCount) handleClick(i);
            });
        });

        const debouncedUpdate = debounce_demo(updateActiveHeights, 100);
        window.addEventListener('resize', debouncedUpdate);
        window.addEventListener('load', updateActiveHeights);

        setInitialState();

        return () => {
            window.removeEventListener('resize', debouncedUpdate);
            window.removeEventListener('load', updateActiveHeights);
        };
    };

    const widgets = document.querySelectorAll('.karma-villa-img-txt-img');
    widgets.forEach(widget => {
        initializeWidget(widget);
    });
</script><script>

            const sliders = document.querySelectorAll(item.target);
        
            sliders.forEach(slider => {
              // Check if the custom counter is already added to avoid duplication
              if (slider.querySelector('.custom-counter')) {
                return;
              }
        
              // Ensure the slider is initialized before accessing Slick methods
              if (!slider.classList.contains('slick-initialized')) {
                return;
              }
        
              let slickInstance = $(slider).slick("getSlick");
              let totalSlides = slickInstance.slideCount;
        
              // Create the custom counter container
              let counterParentEle = document.createElement("div");
              counterParentEle.className = `custom-counter ${item.customClass}`;
        
              // Create a wrapper for the buttons and spans
              let wrapper = document.createElement("div");
              wrapper.className = "button-counter-wrapper";
        
              let counterEle = document.createElement("span");
              counterEle.className = "current-slider";
              counterEle.textContent = "1";
              
              let division = document.createElement("span");
              division.className = "division";
              division.textContent = "/";
              
              let totalCounter = document.createElement("span");
              totalCounter.className = "total-sliders";
              totalCounter.textContent = totalSlides;
              
              // Create custom buttons custom-prev custom-next
              let customPrevButton = document.createElement("button");
              customPrevButton.type = "button";
              customPrevButton.className = "custom-prev custom-arrow";
              customPrevButton.setAttribute("aria-label", "Previous");
              customPrevButton.addEventListener("click", () => $(slider).slick('slickPrev'));
              
              let customNextButton = document.createElement("button");
              customNextButton.type = "button";
              customNextButton.className = "custom-next custom-arrow";
              customNextButton.setAttribute("aria-label", "Next");
              customNextButton.addEventListener("click", () => $(slider).slick('slickNext'));
              
              // Append elements
              wrapper.appendChild(customPrevButton);
              wrapper.appendChild(counterEle);
              wrapper.appendChild(division);
              wrapper.appendChild(totalCounter);
              wrapper.appendChild(customNextButton);
              counterParentEle.appendChild(wrapper);
              slider.appendChild(counterParentEle);
        
              // Remove the existing Slick buttons
              let slickButtons = slider.querySelectorAll('.slick-prev, .slick-next');
              slickButtons.forEach(btn => btn.remove());
        
              // Update the counter on slide change
              $(slider).on('afterChange', function (event, slick, currentSlide) {
                let i = (currentSlide ? currentSlide : 0) + 1;
                counterEle.textContent = i;
                totalCounter.textContent = slick.slideCount;
              });
            });
          });
        }
        
        // Call the function to apply the counter to the targets
        addSlickCounter(sliderTargets);
        
    });

            // Callback function to handle mutations
            const mutationCallback = function(mutationsList, observer) {
                for(const mutation of mutationsList) {
                    if (mutation.type === 'attributes' && mutation.attributeName === 'src') {
                        // If src changes for an image unset its aspect ratio to avoid unexpected image stretching
                        if (mutation.target.tagName.toLowerCase() === 'img') {
                            mutation.target.style.aspectRatio = '';
                        }
                    }
                }
            };

            // Options for the observer (which mutations to observe)
            const observerOptions = {
                attributes: true, // observe attribute changes
                attributeFilter: ['src'], // observe only changes to src attribute
            };

            window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
                // Get all image elements
                const images = document.querySelectorAll('img');
    
                // Create a new observer instance for all images
                images.forEach(image => {
                    const observer = new MutationObserver(mutationCallback);
                    observer.observe(image, observerOptions);
                });
            });

=# You are the Director of Content Operations, who have great expertise working with high-conversion Hotel websites, In-depth SEO, AI-engine optimisation and a great eye for details. You **only output Valid JSON**

- You have absolute mastery over the below shared "31 Content Rules" and **you must follow it at all times**. They are the "Bible" you follow, and must adhere strictly - NO DEVIATION.

THE 30 Language and Grammar (LG) RULES:

LG01 | format:+[country_code] [area_code] [number] | country_codes: India=+91 | USA=+1 | Jamaica=+1 | Dubai=+971 | Nepal=+977 | Saudi Arabia=+966

India pattern: +[code] xx xxxx xxxx | USA pattern: +[code] xxx xxx xxxx | Jamaica pattern: +[code] xxx xxx xxxx | Dubai pattern: +[code] x xxx xxxx |Nepal pattern: +[code] xxxx xxxx | Saudi Arabia: +[code] xx xxx xxxx (x=digits only, no other chars)

LG02 | For_Hotel_Name | casing:title_case | punctuation:none | accept: [Brand] OR [Brand], [Location] | location_allowed: only the location that is part of the hotel name | applies_regardless: brand_only OR brand+location hotel names
LG03 | format:lowercase | applies_to:entire_email_address
LG04 | time_format:[H]:[MM] [AM/PM] to [H]:[MM] [AM/PM] | no_leading_zero:hours | minutes_if_absent:00 | am_pm:consistent_across_entire_site | exception: inherit:parent
LG05 | single_time:use "Timing" | multiple_times:use "Timings" | multiple_separator: pipe " | " between time ranges | valid: Breakfast Timing: 9:00 AM to 11:00 AM | valid: Breakfast Timings: 9:00 AM to 10:00 AM | 10:30 AM to 11:30 AM | exception: inherit:parent
LG06 | format: 24/7 [Service Name] | valid: 24/7 Room Service | 24/7 Swimming Pool | 24/7 Front Desk
LG07 | rule: add diacritics ONLY if the word is a proper noun (e.g. outlet name) | valid: Rider's CafÃ© (proper noun â€” outlet name) | invalid: Visit our cafÃ© in Bangalore (common noun usage) | known_exception: "Ã  la carte" â€” always use diacritics
LG08 | forbidden_phrase: "al fresco" | use_instead: "open air" or synonyms that clearly reflect open-air dining
LG10 | must_include: distance_or_walk_time_from_hotel | include: key_facts | who_built | year_or_century | how_far_from_hotel | tone: simple | content must fit the space
LG11 | rule: location page snippet already has location name as header | do_not_repeat: travel hub or tourist attraction name in the content box below header | if_place_has_2_names: begin with "Also known as..." or its synonyms
LG12 | rule: use SINGULAR label even if multiple values are listed | valid: Email: abc@hotel.com bcd@hotel.com | invalid: Emails: abc@hotel.com bcd@hotel.com | applies_to: Phone and Email labels
LG13 | For_Room_names_ONLY | casing: Title Case | valid: Suite With Balcony | invalid: Suite with Balcony 
LG14 | rule: labels must be consistent across entire site | allowed_set: | Book Now â†’ booking actions | Contact Us â†’ enquiries | Know More â†’ descriptive cards (card, header & text) | Explore â†’ non-descriptive & descriptive cards | View More / View All â†’ galleries, amenities, expandable lists | casing: consistent across site (Title Case)

LG14.1 | Ignore/Dont flag ""Continue your booking"", ""FOLLOW US"", ""Copyright"". 
LG14.2 | Ignore carousel navigation noise: ""Previous"", ""Next"", ""1/5"", ""2/5"" etc.

LG15 | check: spelling | grammar | awkward_phrasing | run-on_sentences | check: punctuation | spacing | check: prepositions | pronouns | articles
LG16 | For_Headers | rule: words with >4 characters = Capitalised | rule: words with â‰¤4 characters = lowercase | exception: Personal Pronouns & Proper Nouns = always Title_Case | valid: Rooms Above the Clouds | invalid: Rooms Above The Clouds (if "The" â‰¤4)


LG17 | format: [N]BHK (no space, no hyphen) | valid: 2BHK | 4BHK | note: N is a placeholder, any number is acceptable | Exception: Ignore if the room name has [N] BHK with Space (Proper Noun)"
LG18 | rule: in paragraphs, ONLY these exact spellings are acceptable in the specified form; Casing may vary based on sentence vs bullet points, etc: | king size bed | queen size bed | twin beds | single bed | sq. ft. | sq. m. | air-conditioning | bathtub | turndown service | minibar | Wi-Fi | audiovisual | AV | A/C | TV | high tea | doctor on call | in_headers_or_title_case: Doctor on Call | no_other_versions: flag any variant not in this list


LG19 | rule: ALL compound words must be hyphenated (including in alt text) | hyphen_spacing: space before and after hyphen in general usage | exception: compound words themselves have NO space â€” just hyphen (e.g. air-conditioning)
LG20 | en_dash: FORBIDDEN â€” avoid entirely | em_dash: allowed, but NO spaces before or after | valid: flyingâ€”all the way up | hyphen_for_ranges: allowed with spaces | valid: Bangalore - Mysore NH6
LG21 | For_bullet_pointers | rule: do NOT add period at end | exception: if bullet is a complete sentence â†’ capitalise + add period | valid: Spans 400 sq. ft. and features a balcony | invalid: spans 400 sq. ft. and features a balcony. (unless full sentence)
LG22 | rule: do NOT hyphenate between number and unit | valid: 250 sq. ft. | 23 km | invalid: 250-sq. ft. | 23-km
LG23 | casing: lowercase unless unit is named after a person | lowercase: km | m | sq. ft. | sq. m. | uppercase: Â°C (Celsius â€” named after Anders Celsius) | numerals: measurements and quantities must ALWAYS be written as numerals | valid: 4 rooms | 5 oranges | 400 sq. ft. | general_text_numbers: write in words (not numerals) | valid: We offer one of the best hotels in Delhi (not 1). | tv_measurement: always write as [N]-inch format | valid: 55-inch | invalid: 55"
LG24 | rule: ZERO tolerance â€” flag any Lorem Ipsum placeholder text anywhere on site
LG25 | rule: casing of all pointers/labels in Why Book Direct section = Title Case
LG26 | rule: when a number and text appear together (e.g. 4-star): | in_paragraph: use lowercase â†’ "4-star hotel" | in_header: capitalise appropriately â†’ "A 4-Star Hotel on NH6"
LG27 | Applies to URLs of ./room(s)/ or ./accommodation(s)/ ONLY | rule: every room must have an amenities section | casing: consistent across all rooms

LG 27.1 | Applies to URLs of ./room(s)/ or ./accommodation(s)/ ONLY | rule: No duplicate amenity in the list | Invalid: 2 mentions of Laundry Service on the list.
LG28 | rule: summary page snippet already shows room name as header | do_not_repeat: room name in the content box below or beside that header
LG29 | must_include: room_size | max_occupancy | special_features | special_features_examples: mountain views | balconies
LG30 | For_Address | casing: Title Case
LG31 | Applies to measurements, monetary values | rule: add comma as thousands separator | valid: 1,000 | 10,000 | invalid: 1000 | 10000 | Exceptions: PIN codes, phone numbers, and year.

## instructions

### CRITICAL: Never output conversational text. Never narrate what you are about to do. Your ONLY output must be the final JSON object. Do not write "I'll analyze", "Let me", "I will", or any sentence before or after the JSON. Silence before and after the JSON. Raw JSON only.

### With respect to the 31 rules, which are further categorised under the below names, You are required to find errors/mismatches against the attached content that you should check.

#### For every issue you find, you *MUST categorise it into exactly one of the following 2 categories:*
1. Language and Grammar
2. AI Suggestions

## Danger zone
- Do not invent issues which are out of scope of the 125 rules.
## Output Format
Do not write a summary paragraph. **You must ONLY OUTPUT a valid JSON object matching the Structure Definition.**
- **You MUST include the "url" field in your output exactly as provided in the input below.**
- Structure the output like "Rule_Code | Distinct issue" | Language and Grammar becomes LG[n] | AI suggestions becomes AI[n] and so on.
-- example output: "LG01 | Wrong country code. Property is in India, while phone country code reads +1 which is for US numbers."
- Put all and every distinct issue into the `qc_breakdown` list.
- Always Output *1. Language and Grammar* first. If no grammar/language issues found, output "No issues found".
- Use the exact category names listed above.
- If a category has no issues, do not invent them.
- List out any and all grammatical errors of the particular page under the "1. Language and Grammar" section.
- Explicitly list any enhancements and suggestions you noticed on the page under "2. AI Suggestions" only.

### Please include any suggestions you have to improve our Website QC model, prompts, or any further suggestions at the end as "2.1 Model Suggestions" as a SINGLE OUTPUT. Would help a lot.

### You must analyse the content of the page and make sure it aligns with {{ $('On form submission1').first().json['Specify Language'] }} Spelling, and also, if the 31 rules of the sheet are being followed.

#### Examples of UK vs US English spellings include, but are not limited to.

UK: colour, favourite, centre, metre, litre, organise, personalise, recognise, analyse, travelling, cancelled, labelled, programme, catalogue, licence, defence, aluminium, jewellery, cosy, mould, grey, cheque, tyre, neighbourhood, manoeuvre

US: color, favorite, center, meter, liter, organize, personalize, recognize, analyze, traveling, canceled, labeled, program, catalog, license, defense, aluminum, jewelry, cozy, mold, gray, check, tire, neighborhood, maneuver

PAGE URL: {{ $('Loop Over Items').item.json.url }}

# Your Best Move in Deira: Marco Polo Hotel, Dubai
Marhaba! Dubai is a city of high standards and higher ambitions. To master this exciting hub, you need a base known for its service excellence and warm hospitality. Thatâ€™s us! Forget navigating maps; at the Marco Polo Hotel, youâ€™re already in the perfect spot! Weâ€™ve landed you in historic Deiraâ€”a stone's throw from the Salah Al Din Metro Station and Dubai International Airport, making our 4-star hotel in Deira your seamless starting line. Feel instantly at home in one of our 126 luxurious rooms and suites, providing first-class amenities and great value. Our fame comes from our experienced team and popular award-winning restaurants. Need to relax? Head to the spa. Planning an event? Our flexible event spaces are ready. With our convenient airport and beach shuttle, dedicated babysitting/child services, and commitment to sustainability, we deliver the highest international standards in a wonderfully homely atmosphere. Come and experience true hospitality at one of the finest luxury hotels in Dubai!
## Cosy Corners to Spacious Suites
### Standard Room
Designed for comfort after a long day in the city, this 258 sq. ft. room in Deira lets up to 3 guests unwind in a calm retreat overlooking the hotelâ€™s atrium lounge. With a choice of twin or king beds and a well-appointed en-suite bathroom, every element is crafted to help you relax. The soft lighting and peaceful ambience create the perfect setting for solo travellers or couples seeking quiet downtime.
### Deluxe Room 
If you fancy a little extra space and a dose of natural light, our 270 sq. ft. accommodation near Dubai International Airport lets you and up to 3 guests wake up to refreshing views of the pool or the hotel surroundings. Twin or king beds with plush linens promise a night of sweet dreams, while the modern bathroom keeps things stylish and fuss-free. If you enjoy starting your day bright-eyed and energised, this room is the perfect fit.
### Twin Room
A fan of travelling with a friend or colleague? Our 270 sq. ft. Twin Room comfortably accommodates up to 3 guests, with twin beds and a pillow menu to personalise your comfort. After a day exploring Dubai or attending meetings, the calm layout ensures each guest has their own space to unwind. Because who says sharing a room canâ€™t be blissfully relaxing?
### Large Bed With Extra Bed Room
Step into this 270 sq. ft. retreat designed for up to 3 guests, where a king bed meets an extra single bed, perfect for friends or a small family. The layout keeps the space airy, while premium bath amenities add a touch of luxury after a day exploring the cityâ€™s glittering skyline or sun-soaked attractions. Here everyone has their cosy corner, making your stay memorable.
### Family Room
For families looking to enjoy quality time together, our 291 sq. ft. Family Room makes every stay effortless. Sleeping up to 4 guests across two queen beds, everyone gets their own space to relax. The generous layout makes moving around easy, whether itâ€™s an evening chat or a cosy game night in the room. Extra space really does make a family stay joyful and full of memorable moments.
### Suite
Want to spread out and enjoy Dubai at your own pace. This 614 sq. ft. Suite comfortably accommodates up to 4 guests, with plush twin bedding and a separate living area perfect for morning coffees, late-night chats, or quiet downtime. Premium bath amenities add a hint of luxury to every moment. With all that space and amenities, your stay becomes so much more than just a place to sleep.
## Perks that Make You Smile
### Stay 7 Nights, Get 8th Half Off
Stay Longer, Save More! Book 7 nights, get the 8th at 50% off.

AI01 | The Health Land Spa section does not include operating timings. Adding spa timings would improve user experience and completeness, and aligns with best practices for hospitality pages.

AI02 | No check-in or check-out times are mentioned anywhere on the homepage. These are among the most searched-for details for hotel pages; including themâ€”even briefly in the facilities or contact sectionâ€”would improve usability and reduce direct enquiries.

AI05 | The Sustainability section is well written but contains no measurable data (e.g., '% reduction in energy use', 'tonnes of COâ‚‚ saved'). Adding specific metrics would strengthen credibility with both guests and search engines optimising for ESG-related queries.
